        "subject": "LU-432 file_operations->fsync no longer get 3 arguments",
        "message": "LU-432 file_operations->fsync no longer get 3 arguments\n\nStarting from kernel 2.6.35 file_operations->fsync needs only 2 arguments,\nleaving the dentry one out. This patch checks whether 3 arguments are\nsupported and if not uses the new 2 argument calls.\n\nChange-Id: I878c6c2752341ce534676334763c611ccf0a6ab8\nSigned-off-by: Christos Triantafyllidis <ctria@grid.auth.gr>\n"
      },
